<div class="teacher-header"><h1>Gemma Binstead</h1><div class="sm"><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/gemma-binstead-439a7a72/"><svg class="icon icon-linkedin"><use xlink:href="#icon-linkedin"></use></svg><span>LinkedIn</span></a> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100004949865094"><svg class="icon icon-facebook2"><use xlink:href="#icon-facebook2"></use></svg><span>Facebook</span></a></div></div><img src="images/teachers/bio-pages/gemma-binstead.jpg" alt="Gemma Binstead" class="w350fr"><p>Gemma has been practising yoga for over 15 years and is qualified with British School of Yoga (BSY) and the Alliance International (2014). Gemma teaches Astanga Primary Series and Transformational Flow Yoga. Both practices are dynamic and flowing, synchronizing breath and movement creating internal heat to cleanse the body. Transformational Yoga combines ancient practices of Hatha, White Tantra, Raja, Mantra, Astanga and Kundalini.</p>